    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black Metallic. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a factory-rated 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M-differential lock. This vehicle has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including a professional subframe reinforcement, VANOS system overhaul, and rod bearing replacement with documented tolerances. The suspension maintains its factory kinematics with zero bushing deflection, and the chassis remains remarkably rigid. Every mechanical component, from the dual-mass flywheel to the cross-drilled rotors, functions at peak performance levels. A turn-key investment for the purist seeking a benchmark-setting analog driving experience.",
